LA_kwDOCVKAsc7iRR1a","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"fef2c0","default":true,"description":"Adding new functionality"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2022-12-26T13:22:03Z","updated_at":"2022-12-26T13:22:24Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"The \"cancel workflow on push\" workflow currently cancels older running copies of a PR CI workflow if a new one is started.\r\n\r\nHowever, this does *not* work as intended if the upper limit of concurrent workflow runs on `sktime` is reached, because the \"cancel workflow on push\" workflow itself is not executed under that condition (as it waits for earlier workflows to terminate).\r\n\r\nIs there a good solution to this?\r\nOne half good solution I can think of is to make the \"cancel workflow on push\" the first step (or second, after linting) of the default CI workflow, i.e., check whether workflows from the same branch are running currently, if yes, cancel them.\r\nOne slightly better solution might check whether *any* workflow runs on `sktime` are currently duplicate, but that might be more involved.\r\n\r\nThere might be even better ideas for this?\r\n\r\nGood first issue for anyone with good CI/CD experience.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/3999/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/3999/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}